# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
athene

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Default sample app
athene-app

# Generated output inside examples/ — the committed source of truth for each
# example is just its form.json + handlers.go; everything else is produced by
# `athene gen` and can be regenerated at any time.
examples/*/app
examples/*/app.gen.go
examples/*/go.mod
examples/*/go.sum
examples/*/Makefile
examples/*/README.md
examples/*/athutil/
examples/*/athui/